title: For Sale/Trade:  Nazi marked Spanish Astra 9mm pistol
postcontent: The Model 600 was made in Spain for Germany during WWII and about 60,000 pistols were made, although only the first 10,500 were delivered before the liberation of France cut off the supply lines between Spain and Germany. The remaining pistols were primarily sold after the war to West Germany for police use, with a smaller number being purchased by Portugal. The gun was rugged and of high quality and accuracy, despite the blowback operation of the gun and heavy weight, it gave a snappy, distinct recoil. This pistol is numbered in the 7000 range and was in the group sold to Germany in 1944.  It was taken off a German soldier in August of 1944 and is a GI bring back. It is mint condition and has the Nazi mark on the right side.  Email for more pictures.  Would sell but would rther trade for a Walther P38.  Let me know what you have.
